    "headline": "How The Moody's (MCO) Investment Narrative Is Shifting As Street Targets Diverge",
    "summary": "Moody's fair value estimate has been nudged from US$535.0 to US$536.0, a small price target adjustment that still matters if you are tracking the stock closely. This tweak sits against a backdrop where bullish analysts are lifting targets by as much as US$30, while more cautious voices are trimming by up to US$100, highlighting how split the Street is on valuation and execution. Read on to see what is driving these opposing calls and how you can follow the evolving Moody's story with more...",
